volunteer_experiences.description:
My main role is to analyse the current status of the education system within the faculty and come with ways of improvising it so that it would help to improve the following:  
- Overall Quality of education;
- Understanding the experiences of all the master students;
- Curriculum, Structure & Syllabus alteration;
- Faculty-student relationships and improvements;
- Quality of the courses (including assignments and exams);

This Ambassadorship involved assisting and helping the new incoming master student succeed at the faculty. It helped the new students to settle in, to act as an informal link between the university and students. The ambassadorship is seen as an important tool for the study success of new MSc students. I was responsible for: 
- Providing information and answer practical questions;
- Pointing students in the right direction for information and support when needed;
- Maintain contact with students during working hours (via WhatsApp and other online platforms);
- Organise an online meeting;
- Organise an informal activity;
- Sharing my university experiences and insights whilst helping new students navigate around the (online) university;
